This paper deals with the problem of vision-based localization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of image retrieval, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
